its%20defenses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EKey%20parts%20of%20territory%20on%20the%20front%20line%20are%20changing%20hands%20daily.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Russian%20tactic%20of%20ceding%20ground%20then%20rapidly%20counterattacking%20is%20proving%20effective%20against%20Ukraine's%20counteroffensive%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F03%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussia-ukraine-elastic-defense-counteroffensive.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tactic%2C%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Belastic%20defense%2C%26quot%3B%20involves%20Russian%20troops%20withdrawing%20from%20a%20trench%20to%20a%20secondary%20defensive%20position%20once%20it%20comes%20under%20fire%20from%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20then%20counterattack%20when%20Ukrainian%20troops%20are%20approaching%20the%20abandoned%20trench%20or%20have%20just%20arrived%2C%20and%20are%20vulnerable%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20defender%20gives%20ground%20while%20inflicting%20as%20heavy%20casualties%20as%20they%20can%20on%20the%20attackers%20with%20a%20view%20to%20being%20able%20to%20set%20the%20attackers%20up%20for%20a%20decisive%20counterattack%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20analyst%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20description%20was%20from%20Ben%20Barry%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20for%20land%20war%20studies%20at%20the%20International%20Institute%20for%20Strategic%20Studies%2C%20who%20spoke%20to%20The%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20weeks%2C%20there%20has%20been%20intense%20fighting%20in%20the%20southern%20Zaporizhzhia%20region%20as%20Ukraine%20seeks%20to%20capitalise%20on%20its%20success%20in%20seizing%20control%20of%20the%20village%20of%20Robotyne%20and%20make%20a%20decisive%20break%20through%20Russian%20defenses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20aim%20of%20the%20Russian%20tactics%2C%20said%20The%20Times%2C%20is%20to%20prevent%20Ukraine%20from%20gaining%20a%20foothold%20which%20it%20could%20rapidly%20reinforce%20with%20armored%20vehicles%20and%20use%20to%20launch%20further%20attacks.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Institute%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.understandingwar.org%2Fbackgrounder%2Frussian-offensive-campaign-assessment-october-1-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStudy%20of%20War%2C%20a%20US%20think%20tanks%20that%20analyses%20the%20conflict%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20trench%20systems%20were%20frequently%20changing%20hands%20amid%20intense%20fighting%20near%20the%20village%20of%20Robotyne.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20assess%20that%20Russia%20was%20using%20successful%20counterattacks.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.in%2Finternational%2Fnews%2Fan-elite-russian-units-morale-is-at-critical-levels-after-being-sent-to-stop-ukraines-counteroffensive-analysts-say%2Farticleshow%2F104134300.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EISW%2C%20Russia%20has%20deployed%20elite%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20counterattacks%20that%20have%20sustained%20heavy%20casualties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-elastic-defense-tactic-is-effective-against-ukraine-nyt-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696422286000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651d4ed5617692f0d03e9c29%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-elastic-defense-tactic-is-effective-against-ukraine-nyt-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russia%20has%20adapted%20its%20tactics%20as%20it%20seeks%20to%20prevent%20Ukraine%20making%20a%20decisive%20breakthrough%20in%20its%20defensive%20positions%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tporter%40businessinsider.com%20(Tom%20Porter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinside