%3E%3Cp%3EA%20judge%20dismissed%20a%20lawsuit%20that%20said%20McDonald's%20and%20Wendy's%20burgers%20looked%20much%20bigger%20in%20ads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%2C%20filed%20in%20May%202022%20by%20Justin%20Chimienti%2C%20accused%20the%20fast-food%20chains%20of%20%26quot%3Bunfair%20and%20deceptive%20trade%20practices%2C%26quot%3B%20saying%20that%20they%20%26quot%3Bfalsely%20advertised%26quot%3B%20some%20of%20their%20menu%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20said%20that%20McDonald's%20and%20Wendy's%20both%20overstated%20the%20size%20of%20their%20beef%20patties%20in%20their%20adverts%20for%20nearly%20every%20product%2C%20with%20a%20particular%20focus%20on%20Wendy's%20Bourbon%20Bacon%20Cheeseburger.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chains%20used%20photos%20of%20patties%20that%20weren't%20fully%20cooked%20%26quot%3Bto%20make%20it%20appear%20that%20they%20are%20approximately%2015-20%25%20larger%20than%20the%20beef%20patties%20that%20are%20actually%20served%20to%20customers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20meat%20generally%20shrinks%20by%20a%20quarter%20when%20cooked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%2C%20filed%20in%20the%20Eastern%20District%20of%20New%20York%2C%20cited%20social-media%20reviews%20from%20YouTube%20and%20X%20users%20who%20complained%20that%20their%20burgers%20were%20smaller%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWendy's%20adverts%20also%20exaggerated%20the%20amount%20of%20the%20toppings%20its%20burgers%20featured%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20said%2C%20without%20giving%20specifics.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChimienti%20said%20that%20he'd%20bought%20a%20Bourbon%20Bacon%20Cheeseburger%20and%20a%20Big%20Bacon%20Cheddar%20Cheeseburger%20from%20Wendy's%20and%20a%20Big%20Mac%20and%20a%20cheeseburger%20from%20McDonald's.%20He%20said%20that%20he%20expected%20the%20burgers%20to%20be%20similar%20in%20size%20to%20the%20pictures%20of%20the%20burgers%20in%20adverts%20but%20that%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20smaller%20than%20advertised.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22760%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20advert%20for%20Wendy's%20Bourbon%20Bacon%20Cheeseburger%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651d3e3e42ecf94db477628e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22427%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20advert%20for%20Wendy's%20Bourbon%20Bacon%20Cheeseburger.%3Cp%3EWendy's%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20four-count%20lawsuit%20asked%20for%20punitive%20and%20compensatory%20damages%20as%20well%20as%20an%20order%20for%20the%20chains%20to%20stop%20selling%20the%20burgers%20or%20to%20change%20their%20adverts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcDonald's%20and%20Wendy's%20filed%20motions%20to%20dismiss%20the%20lawsuit%20last%20September.%20US%20District%20Judge%20Hector%20Gonzalez%20granted%20the%20chains'%20motion%20on%20September%2030%2C%202023%2C%20which%20he%20said%20was%20%26quot%3Bprincipally%20because%20the%20advertisements%20were%20not%20misleading%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGonzalez%20said%20in%20his%20decision%20that%20Chimienti%20had%20not%20stated%20in%20the%20lawsuit%20that%20he%20actually%20saw%20adverts%20for%20burgers%20from%20McDonald's%20and%20Wendy's%20prior%20to%20buying%20them%2C%20nor%20did%20he%20refer%20at%20all%20to%20adverts%20for%20two%20of%20the%20burgers%20he%20purchased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChimienti%20also%20%26quot%3Bfails%20adequately%20to%20allege%20that%20a%20reasonable%20customer%20would%20likely%20be%20misled%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20adverts%20about%20the%20size%20of%20the%20burgers%2C%20Gonzalez%20wrote%2C%20noting%20that%20both%20McDonald's%20and%20Wendy's%20websites%20list%20their%20calorie%20content%20while%20Wendy's%20also%20lists%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wendys.com%2Fblog%2Fbourbon-bacon-cheeseburger-is-menu-innovation-at-its-finest%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweight%20of%20the%20patties%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20has%20commented%20Chimienti's%20lawyers%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp