ore%2C%20easy%20to%20understand%20%E2%80%93%20I%20strongly%20suggest%20you%20watch%20the%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20you%2C%20I%20include%20the%20list%20of%20questions%20asked%20so%20that%20you%20can%20see%20how%20the%20interview%20is%20structured.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20questions%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E1)%20In%20a%20recent%20op-ed%20that%20you%20wrote%20for%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20(28%2F9)%20you%20say%20that%3A%20%E2%80%9CHeadline%20GDP%20is%20a%20dangerously%20misleading%20odometer%20for%20the%20economic%20engine%20of%20a%20nation.%E2%80%9D%20In%20other%20words%2C%20Headline%20GDP%20does%20not%20tell%20you%20the%20true%20condition%20in%20which%20the%20majority%20of%20people%20live.%20You%20can%20have%20high%20GDP%20growth%20but%20also%20worryingly%20high%20unemployment%20and%20tens%20of%20millions%20dependent%20on%20NREGA.%20Have%20I%20understood%20you%20correctly%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E2)%C2%A0%20Now%20two%20things%20follow%20from%20what%20you%20have%20written.%20First%20%E2%80%93%20and%20this%20may%20be%20incidental%20or%20tangential%20%E2%80%93%20the%20debate%20between%20four%20Chief%20Economic%20Advisors%2C%20three%20foreign%20university%20academics%20and%20members%20of%20the%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20over%20India%E2%80%99s%20actual%20GDP%20growth%20rate%20for%20the%20last%20quarter%20and%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20strong%20or%20anemic%20is%20irrelevant%20because%20GDP%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20convey%20the%20real%20truth%20about%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E3)%20The%20second%20point%20is%20more%20important.%20India%E2%80%99s%20quarter%201%20GDP%20growth%20of%207.8%25%20more%20or%20less%20coincided%20with%20the%20highest%20ever%20demand%20during%20the%20last%2010%20years%20for%20NREGA%20in%20June%2C%20July%20and%20August%20as%20well%20as%20an%20unemployment%20rate%20hovering%20around%208%25.%20This%20means%20impressive%20GDP%20growth%20and%20very%20distressing%20unemployment%20and%20economic%20distress%20can%20occur%20at%20the%20same.%20Unemployment%3A%207.9%25%20July%20and%208.1%25%20August%20(CMIE).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E4)%20Let%E2%80%99s%20drill%20a%20little%20further%20into%20this%20point.%20In%20August%2C%2020%20million%20families%20were%20dependent%20on%20NREGA.%20This%20means%2C%20as%20you%20put%20it%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmillions%20of%20families%20are%20signaling%20that%2C%20as%20recently%20as%20a%20few%20weeks%20ago%2C%20they%20had%20no%20other%20source%20of%20income%20except%20to%20toil%20for%20bare%20minimum%20wages%20under%20the%20NREGA%20unemployment%20insurance%20scheme%20%E2%80%A6%20it%20is%20an%20indicator%20of%20the%20economic%20distress%20of%20Indian%20households.%E2%80%9D%20And%20this%20happened%20%E2%80%9Cjust%20when%20India%E2%80%99s%20economy%20apparently%20experienced%20one%20of%20its%20strongest%20growth%20quarters%E2%80%9D.%20So%20we%20have%20huge%20distress%20which%20is%20masked%20or%2C%20at%20least%2C%20not%20revealed%20by%20the%20soaring%20GDP%20figure.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E5)%C2%A0%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20further%20point%20about%20GDP%20which%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20make%20in%20your%20article%20but%20let%20me%20put%20it%20to%20you%20to%20see%20if%20you%20agree.%20GDP%20uses%20a%20proxy%20to%20estimate%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20in%20the%20unorganized%20sector%20which%20is%2045%25%20(including%20agriculture)%20of%20the%20economy%20and%2080-85%25%20of%20employment.%20So%2C%20first%20of%20all%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20sure%20if%20it%E2%80%99s%20being%20measured%20correctly.%20Second%2C%20if%20the%20unorganized%20sector%20is%20disproportionately%20hit%20by%20COVID-19%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20organised%20sector%2C%20the%20proxy%20which%20is%20derived%20from%20the%20organized%20sector%20will%20very%20substantially%20overestimate%20the%20unorganised%20sector.%20Do%20you%20agree%20this%20is%20another%20reason%20why%20GDP%20is%20misleading%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E6)%20Now%20you%20come%20to%20two%20conclusions.%20First%2C%20you%20say%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20idea%20of%20GDP%20as%20a%20holy%20grail%20measure%20for%20the%20health%20of%20the%20overall%20economy%E2%80%9D%20is%20not%20just%20misleading%20but%20close%20to%20meaningless.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E7)%20Your%20second%20conclusion%20is%20actually%20a%20message%20to%20the%20Opposition%20Block%20INDIA.%20You%20say%3A%20%E2%80%9CInstead%20of%20nit-picking%20on%20GDP%20numbers%20as%20they%20normally%20do%2C%20the%20Opposition%20INDIA%20alliance%20can%20start%20by%20rejecting%20next%20quarter%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20release%20and%20instead%20demand%20data%20on%20median%20income%20growth%20and%20the%20total%20number%20of%20jobs%20created%20in%20the%20economy.%E2%80%9D%20This%2C%20I%20presume%2C%20would%20be%20a%20way%20of%20talking%20about%20what%20matters%20to%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20Indian%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E8)%20Have%20you%20discussed%20this%20advice%20with%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20or%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E9)%20In%20fact%2C%20you%20go%20one%20step%20further.%20You%20also%20have%20a%20general%20message%20for%20those%20who%20write%20about%20or%20claim%20to%20understand%20the%20economy.%20You%20say%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20time%20for%20a%20complete%20reset%20in%20our%20economic%20public%20discourse%20and%20narrative%20%E2%80%A6%20the%20health%20of%20the%20labour%20markets%20has%20to%20shape%20the%20economic%20narrative%20of%20the%20nation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E10)%20Finally%2C%20what%20you%20say%20about%20India%20is%20actually%20true%20for%20most%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20You%20say%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20correlation%20between%20Headline%20GDP%20and%20prosperity%20for%20the%20median%20citizen%20has%20broken%20in%20most%20nations.%E2%80%9D%20In%20other%20words%2C%20in%20a%20sense%2C%20your%20advice%20applies%20universally.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696417145000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F04161946%2FKT-4-OCtober.00_29_16_07.Still001.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22htt