fining%20feature%20of%20land%20warfare%20for%20over%20a%20century%2C%20and%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20no%20exception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThousands%20of%20tanks%20and%20armored%20vehicles%20have%20been%20destroyed%20since%20Russia%20attacked%20in%20February%202022.%20An%20unusual%20feature%20of%20that%20fighting%20has%20been%20that%20both%20sides%20are%20using%20the%20same%20or%20similar%20models%20of%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20commonality%20is%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20Soviet%20military's%20lasting%20legacy.%20While%20updated%20variants%20and%20new%20models%20have%20been%20introduced%20since%20the%20Soviet%20disintegration%20in%201991%2C%20most%20of%20the%20tanks%20being%20used%20in%20Ukraine%20were%20designed%20%E2%80%94%20and%20many%20of%20them%20built%20%E2%80%94%20during%20the%20Cold%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20may%20not%20be%20surprising%20that%20old%20tanks%20have%20vulnerabilities%2C%20nearly%20two%20years%20of%20combat%20have%20put%20their%20outdated%20qualities%20on%20full%20display.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ET-72s%2C%20T-80s%2C%20and%20T-90s%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20loading%20a%20tank%20onto%20a%20truck.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6331f61c2675740018b51b40%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainians%20load%20a%20Russian%20T-72%20onto%20a%20truck%20outside%20Izyum%20in%20September%202022.%3Cp%3EANATOLII%20STEPANOV%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20common%20tank%20at%20the%20front%20has%20been%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.armyrecognition.com%2Frussia_russian_army_tank_heavy_armoured_vehicles_u%2Ft-72a_t-72_a_main_battle_tank_technical_data_fact_sheet_pictures.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ET-72%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Introduced%20in%201973%2C%20it's%20the%20backbone%20of%20the%20Russian%20armored%20corps%20an