20of%20resources%20as%20an%20excuse%20to%20harm%20borrowers%20in%20repayment.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%20of%20Massachusetts%20was%20keeping%20an%20eye%20on%20the%20student-loan%20industry%20even%20before%20she%20became%20a%20lawmaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20professor%20at%20Harvard%20Law%20School%20in%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20she%20studied%20the%20impact%20of%20debt%20on%20Americans%20%E2%80%94%20and%20later%20spearheaded%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20in%202011%2C%20which%20has%20since%20enacted%20strict%20oversight%20of%20the%20federal%20student-loan%20industry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20industry%20has%20a%20horrible%20track%20record%2C%26quot%3B%20Warren%20told%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview.%20%26quot%3BTheir%20failure%20to%20serve%20students%20has%20dated%20back%20decades.%20We%20uncovered%20evidence%20of%20student-loan%20errors%20and%20refusal%20to%20help%20students%20before%20I%20even%20got%20to%20the%20Senate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20focus%20on%20the%20industry%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcan-student-loan-borrowers-discharge-debt-bankruptcy-doj-elizabeth-warren-2023-7%5C%22%3Estrengthened%3C%2Fa%3E%20once%20she%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20Senate%20in%202012%20%E2%80%94%20since%20then%2C%20she%20has%20become%20a%20leading%20voice%20on%20accountability%20for%20companies%20that%20service%20student%20debt%20and%20has%20pushed%20for%20broad%20forgiveness.%20While%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-cancels-student-loan-debt-100000-people-making-125k-income-2022-5%3Fesd%5C%22%3Einitial%20plan%20to%20cancel%20up%20to%20%2420%2C000%20in%20student%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20federal%20borrowers%20fell%20short%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcancel-student-loan-debt-elizabeth-warren-only-sin-check-biden-2022-3%5C%22%3EWarren's%20push%20for%20%2450%2C000%20in%20relief%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20threw%20her%20support%20behind%20it%20and%20later%20criticized%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-blocked-supreme-court-strikes-down-debt-cancellation-2023-5%5C%22%3Estriking%20it%20down%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Education%20Department%20announced%20a%20plan%20to%20pursue%20broad%20debt%20relief%20using%20a%20different%20law%2C%20but%20Warren%20said%20she's%20worried%20the%20new%20push%20would%20face%20the%20same%20fate%20in%20the%20conservative-majority%20court.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Supreme%20Court%20failed%20to%20follow%20the%20explicit%20language%20of%20the%20law%20and%20turned%20his%20efforts%20upside%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20Warren%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20raises%20serious%20concerns%20for%20whatever%20comes%20next.%20I'm%20glad%20that%20the%20administration%20is%20going%20through%20negotiated%20rulemaking%2C%20but%20an%20extremist%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20fails%20to%20follow%20the%20law%20threatens%20that%20process%20no%20matter%20how%20clearly%20legal%20it%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-long-will-take-cancel-student-debt-higher-education-act-2023-7%5C%22%3ENegotiated%20rulemaking%3C%2Fa%3E%20includes%20a%20series%20of%20negotiation%20sessions%20with%20stakeholders%20to%20craft%20the%20new%20debt-relief%20plan%20using%20the%20Higher%20Education%20Act%20of%201965%2C%20along%20with%20an%20opportunity%20for%20the%20public%20to%20comment%20on%20it.%20It'll%20likely%20take%20at%20least%20a%20year%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20guarantee%20it'll%20be%20free%20of%20legal%20challenges.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20court%20today%20that%20has%20jumped%20the%20boundaries%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20and%20that%20undermines%20every%20effort%20that%20the%20federal%20government%20takes%20on%20that%20might%20conflict%20with%20the%20political%20views%20of%20the%20extremists%20on%20the%20court%2C%26quot%3B%20Warren%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20think%20the%20Biden%20administration%20is%20doing%20the%20right%20thing.%20But%20yes%2C%20I%20am%20concerned%20about%20what%20this%20court%20will%20ultimately%20do%20with%20Biden's%20rulemaking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20need%20for%20bolstered%20oversight%20of%20student-loan%20companies%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20broad%20student-loan%20forgiveness%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-repayment-issues-debt-relief-broken-industry-2023-9%5C%22%3Ethe%20most%20pressing%20issue%20facing%20millions%20of%20federal%20borrowers%20is%20the%20return%20to%20repayment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20September%2C%20interest%20began%20accruing%20again%20on%20balances%20after%20an%20over%20three-year%20pause%2C%20and%20bills%20started%20becoming%20due%20this%20month.%20But%20in%20the%20months%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20transition%2C%20many%20borrowers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-payments-resume-confusion-borrowers-debt-relief-biden-2023-8%5C%22%3Ereported%20issues%20with%20their%20servicers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%20hourslong%20hold%20times%20with%20customer%20service%20to%20errors%20with%20their%20billing%20statements.%20One%20borrower%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-afford-student-loan-payments-borrowers-sells-ebay-debt-2023-9%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20gearing%20up%20for%20repayment%20had%20left%20her%20feeling%20%26quot%3Btremendously%20hopeless.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20issue%20Warren%20said%20she's%20watching%20closely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20student-loan%20servicers%20are%20giving%20bad%20advice%2C%20putting%20people%20in%20the%20wrong%20repayment%20programs%2C%20and%20making%20mistakes%20in%20what%20they%20charge%2C%20it%20takes%20a%20terrible%20problem%20and%20makes%20it%20100-fold%20worse%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI've%20talked%20to%20many%20people%20who%20were%20in%20tears%20over%20the%20frustrations%20they%20felt%20with%20their%20student-loan%20servicers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOversight%20is%20a%20key%20thing%20the%20industry%20has%20been%20lacking%2C%20Warren%20said.%20She%20credits%20the%20Biden%20administration%20with%20%26quot%3Bweeding%20out%20some%20of%20the%20truly%20bad%20apples%20in%20the%20industry%26quot%3B%20but%20said%20more%20needed%20to%20be%20done.%20Servicers%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-company-mohela-extensive-servicing-delays-repayment-borrowers-warren-2023-9%5C%22%3Ecast%20the%20blame%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20lack%20of%20resources%20from%20the%20Education%20Department.%20While%20Biden%20has%20asked%20Congress%20for%20more%20Federal%20Student%20Aid%20funding%20to%20help%20administer%20the%20repayment%20programs%2C%20House%20Republicans%20have%20proposed%20funding%20cuts%20for%20the%20office%2C%20which%20some%20servicers%20have%20said%20would%20leave%20them%20without%20enough%20staff%20to%20manage%20the%20influx%20of%20daily%20borrower%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarren%2C%20however%2C%20isn't%20convinced%20by%20that%20argument.%20She%20said%20servicers%20continued%20to%20receive%20funding%20during%20the%20pandemic%20even%20when%20millions%20of%20borrowers%20were%20not%20making%20payments%20and%20that%20because%20of%20that%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20should%20now%20be%20fully%20prepared%20to%20meet%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20students%20as%20the%20repayment%20plans%20are%20turned%20back%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20them%20to%20come%20in%20now%20and%20cry%20poverty%20because%20it's%20hard%20to%20send%20out%20accurate%20bills%20to%20people%20who%20owe%20money%20does%20not%20prompt%20much%20sympathy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20signed%20contracts%20to%20administer%20the%20loan%20system%20accurately.%20Those%20are%20profitable%20contracts.%20But%20the%20servicers%20want%20even%20more%20money%3F%20I%20have%20no%20sympathy%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-elizabeth-warren-serious-concerns-broad-debt-relief-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696413781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F623c971ca2e45b0019503001%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-elizabeth-warren-serious-concerns-broad-debt-relief-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Warren%20is%20not%20sympathetic%20to%20student-loan%20companies%20who%20%26quot%3Bcry%20poverty%26quot%3B%20when%20they%20can't%20handle%20all%20borrowers'%20requests%2C%20she%20told%20Insider.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-elizabeth-warren-serious-concerns-broad-debt-relief-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Kapil%20Sibal%20Thinks%20Electoral%20Reforms%2C%20EVM%20'Totalisers'%20Are%20Necessities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F11%2F16133352%2Fkapil-sibal-congress.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20raucous%20debate%20around%20%E2%80%98One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Poll%E2%80%99%20and%20other%20electoral%20amendments%20and%20reforms%2C%20a%20significant%20electoral%20transgression%20that%20is%20studiously%20ignored%20and%20always%20put%20aside%20is%20the%20unsettled%20issue%20of%20declaring%20booth-wise%20results%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(EC).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20consequences%20of%20knowing%20how%20a%20booth%2C%20which%20represents%20a%20clutch%20of%20streets%2C%20has%20voted%20not%20only%20goes%20against%20the%20principle%20of%20secret%20ballot%20but%20is%20lethal%20and%20destructive%20when%20threats%2C%20harassment%20and%20intimidation%20are%20used%20by%20political%20parties%20to%20force%20a%20voter%20to%20go%20their%20way.%20The%20only%20safeguard%20is%20to%20get%20a%20totaliser%2C%20which%20has%20been%20developed%20by%20the%20EC%20to%20be%20attached%20to%20the%20EVM.%20Eminent%20lawyer%20and%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20first%20with%20the%20Congress%20and%20now%20with%20ally%20Samajwadi%20Party%2C%20outlines%20the%20road%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EExcerpts%20from%20the%20interview%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20agree%20with%20the%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20from%202008%2C%20to%20get%20totalisers%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20has%20changed%20today%2C%20and%20unfortunately%20that%20recommendation%20which%20was%20extremely%20significant%20for%20the%20Election%20Commission%20to%20ensure%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%2C%20the%20EC%20today%20is%20in%20complete%20alignment%20with%20the%20present%20government.%20So%2C%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20expect%20anything%20from%20the%20EC%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETotalisers%20are%20crucial%20as%20they%20prevent%20political%20parties%20from%20getting%20booth-wise%20results%2C%20which%20goes%20against%20the%20principle%20of%20secret%20ballot%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20for%20electoral%20fairness%2C%20it%20is%20crucial%20political%20parties%20are%20not%20allowed%20to%20manipulate%20results%2C%20and%20a%20totaliser%20would%20have%20ensured%20that%20political%20parties%20have%20no%20access%20to%20find%20out%20how%20citizens%20have%20voted%20and%20for%20which%20party%20in%20any%20particular%20booth.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20totaliser%20in%20an%20EVM%20mixes%20up%20votes%2C%20like%20in%20the%20pre-EVM%20age%20of%20paper%20ballots%2C%20thus%20making%20it%20impossible%20to%20find%20out%20how%20a%20booth%20voted%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%20introduction%20of%20EVMs%2C%20ballot%20papers%20could%20be%20mixed%20if%20there%20was%20any%20apprehension%20of%20intimidation%20of%20voters.%20Therefore%2C%20if%20political%20parties%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20access%20to%20booth-wise%20results%2C%20they%20cannot%20pressurise%20or%20threaten%20those%20particular%20voters%20of%20the%20locality%20who%20didn%E2%80%99t%20vote%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20EC%20recommendation%20came%20when%20your%20government%20UPA%20II%20was%20in%20power%2C%20but%20nothing%20happened%20despite%20the%20setting%20up%20of%20a%20parliamentary%20committee%20to%20look%20into%20it.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20parliamentary%20committee%20was%20set%20up%20in%202009%2C%20but%20it%20reached%20nowhere%E2%80%A6%20however%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20the%20Congress%20party%20would%20have%20opposed%20the%20idea%2C%20most%20political%20parties%20and%20allies%20were%20in%20alignment%20with%20this%20recommendation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20think%20we%20really%20didn%E2%80%99t%20realise%20the%20significance%20or%20the%20importance%20of%20this%20necessity%20then%2C%20the%20enormity%20of%20the%20situation%20came%20to%20us%20later%2C%20in%202014%20after%20the%20new%20government%20came%20to%20power.%20It%20has%20been%20stonewalling%20the%20recommendation%20of%20totalisers%20and%20has%20not%20come%20forward%20to%20support%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20August%202014%2C%20after%20the%20Modi%20government%20came%20to%20power%2C%20the%20EC%20moved%20the%20law%20ministry%20yet%20again%2C%20but%20it%20was%20only%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20took%20note%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20PIL%20in%20September%20the%20same%20year%2C%20that%20the%20issue%20was%20in%20the%20spotlight%20again.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20correct%2C%20the%20PIL%20has%20been%20asking%20the%20government%20what%20it%20intends%20to%20do%3B%20after%20all%2C%20the%20EC%20can%E2%80%99t%20formally%20say%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20agree%20with%20its%20own%20recommendations.%20The%20EC%20today%20is%20obviously%20not%20pushing%20for%20it%2C%20nor%20is%20the%20government%20very%20keen%20on%20it%20and%20the%20issue%20is%20lying%20in%20limbo.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20January%202017%2C%20a%20group%20of%20ministers%20headed%20by%20Rajnath%20Singh%2C%20that%20included%20Arun%20Jaitley%2C%20Manohar%20Parrikar%20and%20others%2C%20rejected%20the%20introduction%20of%20totalisers%20saying%20booth%20management%20helps%20parties%20to%20be%20responsive%20to%20people%E2%80%99s%20needs.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20GoP%20rejected%20totalisers%20saying%20machines%20are%20involved%20and%20so%20they%20can%E2%80%99t%20interfere%2C%20and%20other%20reasons%20mentioned%20above%2C%20but%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20mention%20(of%20the%20danger)%20of%20knowing%20voter%20results.%20As%20I%20said%2C%20this%20government%20is%20not%20at%20all%20keen%20on%20totalisers%20because%20it%20wants%20to%20collect%20booth%20data%20for%20the%20purposes%20of%20pressurising%20the%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20the%20well-known%20case%20where%20BJP%20MP%20Maneka%20Gandhi%20publicly%20said%20at%20election%20rallies%20that%20development%20will%20be%20cut%20off%20going%20by%20booth%20results.%20So%20did%20Tejasvi%20Surya%2C%20who%20showed%20how%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%20vote%2C%20from%20booth%20results.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20the%20tactics%20they%20use%20to%20manipulate%20the%20results%2C%20and%20pollute%20the%20election%20process.%20The%20BJP%20or%20any%20political%20party%20knows%20from%20booth-wise%20results%20that%20in%20this%20particular%20area%2C%20the%20voters%20are%20with%20us%20or%20against%20us.%20Post-election%20too%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20easy%20to%20find%20out%20voting%20trends%20from%20booth%20results%2C%20politicians%20can%20intimidate%20and%20threaten%20as%20Maneka%20warned%20voters%20during%20her%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20ways%20to%20cut%20out%20your%20anti-vote%20by%20looking%20at%20past%20voting%20trends%20from%20booths%20%E2%80%93%20eliminate%20or%20delete%20names%20from%20electoral%20rolls%3B%20only%20one%20Aadhaar%20card%20is%20reflected%20and%20not%20of%20the%20others%20in%20a%20family%3B%20then%20they%20find%20homes%20that%20have%20been%20vacated%20but%20members%20are%20still%20on%20the%20voter%20rolls%20and%20votes%20are%20cast%20in%20their%20names%20after%205%20pm%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20person%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20polling%20booths.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EManipulation%20of%20EVMs%20is%20a%20very%20unpopular%20allegation%20because%20nobody%20can%20actually%20prove%20it%2C%20but%20either%20way%2C%20the%20presumption%20is%20that%20any%20machine%20can%20be%20manipulated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20also%20have%20a%20prime%20minister%20today%20who%20blows%20up%20hundreds%20of%20crores%20of%20taxpayers%E2%80%99%20money%20on%20his%20election%20campaigns.%20Does%20that%20give%20him%20an%20unfair%20advantage%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsn%E2%80%99t%20it%20up%20to%20the%20EC%20to%20take%20note%20of%20what%E2%80%99s%20going%20on%3F%20If%20institutional%20processes%20don%E2%80%99t%20work%2C%20then%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20will%20do%20what%20he%20wants%20to%20do%2C%20unhindered.%20The%20institutional%20processes%20in%20this%20country%20have%20been%20dismantled%2C%20so%20obviously%20there%20is%20no%20institutional%20check%20on%20activities.%20Every%20institutional%20structure%20has%20been%20systematically%20dismantled%2C%20including%20of%20course%2C%20the%20EC%2C%20which%20is%20a%20collaborator%20in%20this%20enterprise%20today.%20We%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20the%20EC%20watching%20with%20complete%20disregard%20when%20in%20one%20constituency%20the%20voting%20is%20going%20on%20and%20next%20door%2C%20in%20another%20state%20where%20the%20election%20is%20going%20on%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20is%20making%20an%20election%20appeal%20which%20is%20being%20televised.%20The%20EC%20is%20quiet%20and%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20send%20notices%20when%20ministers%20and%20political%20leaders%20make%20disparaging%20remarks%20and%20threaten%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20mainstream%20media%20too%20is%20a%20very%20active%20collaborator%20with%20the%20BJP%2C%20these%20are%20institutional%20structures%20that%20have%20been%20dismantled%20for%20reasons%20of%20greed%20%E2%80%93%20for%20high%20TRPs%2C%20and%20where%20industrial%20houses%20which%20own%20the%20media%20seek%20favours%20from%20the%20government%20on%20a%20daily%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20too%20much%20hope%20in%20the%20institutions%20waking%20up%20to%20their%20responsibilities.%20and%20I%20sincerely%20hope%20the%20court%20intervenes%20and%20takes%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20journalists%2C%20human%20rights%20activists%2C%20academics%2C%20students%20have%20also%20been%20picked%20up%20and%20thrown%20into%20prison.%20And%20hate%20speakers%20are%20simply%20let%20off%20the%20hook%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20look%20at%20the%20hate%20economy%20all%20the%20time.%20We%20are%20filing%20petition%20after%20petition%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20almost%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%2C%20like%20on%20the%20dharam%20sansad%20etc%2C%20but%20very%20little%20has%20come%20out%20of%20it.%20Why%20should%20hate%20speeches%20have%20to%20go%20to%20court%3F%20The%20process%20is%20simple%20%E2%80%93%20wherever%20a%20hate%20speech%20is%20made%2C%20the%20local%20administration%20should%20move%20in%2C%20file%20an%20FIR%2C%20investigate%20the%20case%2C%20and%20people%20punished.%20All%20these%20hate%20speeches%20are%20made%20mostly%20in%20areas%20where%20the%20BJP%20is%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20just%20got%20a%20couple%20of%20orders%20from%20Justice%20KM%20Joseph%2C%20he%E2%80%99s%20retired%20now.%20Justice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20is%20looking%20at%20matters%20today%2C%20he%20has%20taken%20some%20effective%20steps%2C%20hope%20it%20works%20out.%20Justice%20Khanna%20is%20also%20in%20line%20to%20be%20the%20next%20chief%20justice%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20pick%20up%20journalists%2C%20activists%2C%20academics%2C%20students%2C%20and%20members%20of%20the%20minority%20communities%2C%20those%20who%20speak%20against%20the%20government%20and%20voice%20dissent.%20Most%20of%20them%20are%20of%20course%20without%20any%20basis%2C%20but%20they%20foist%20cases%20on%20them%2C%20from%20sedition%20to%20causing%20enmity%20etc%20under%20sections%20153%20A%2C%20298%20A%20of%20the%20IPC.%20Cases%20are%20lodged%20against%20people%20based%20on%20all%20kinds%20of%20conspiracy%20theories%20which%20have%20no%20basis%20at%20all%2C%20but%20court%20procedures%20take%20a%20lot%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20the%20safeguards%20then%2C%20to%20ensure%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20poll%20before%202024%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20hope%20is%20the%20court.%20We%20should%20go%20back%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20we%20will%20file%20a%20comprehensive%20petition%20for%20electoral%20reform%20to%20make%20the%20process%20of%20election%20fair%2C%20which%20will%20of%20course%2C%20include%20the%20insistence%20on%20a%20totaliser.%20I%20think%20the%20court%20and%20political%20parties%20must%20rule%20in%20favour%20of%20totalisers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20to%20also%20see%20how%20they%20manipulate%20the%20election%20results%2C%20the%20deletion%20of%20people%20on%20the%20electoral%20roll%2C%20deletion%20of%20families%20or%20particular%20communities.%20Or%2C%20how%20the%20administration%20and%20the%20police%20forces%20disallow%20people%20to%20go%20out%20and%20vote%2C%20the%20EVMs%2C%20the%20paper%20trail%2C%20etc.%20It%E2%80%99s%20time%20to%20wake%20up%20the%20nation%20on%20all%20these%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696413614000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F11%2F16133352%2Fkapil-sibal-congress.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhy-kapil-sibal-thinks-electoral-reforms-evm-totalisers-are-necessities%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BFor%20electoral%20fairness%2C%20it%20is%20crucial%20political%20parties%20are%20not%20allowed%20to%20manipulate%20results%2C%20and%20a%20totaliser%20would%20have%20ensured%20that%20political%20parties%20have%20no%20access%20to%20find%20out%20how%20citizens%20have%20voted%20and%20for%20which%20party%20in%20any%20particular%20booth.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhy-kapil-sibal-thinks-electoral-reforms-evm-totalisers-are-necessities%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Moungi%20Bawendi%2C%20Louis%20Brus%2C%20Alexei%20Ekimov%20Get%20Nobel%20Prize%20For%20Chemistry%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMoungi%20Bawendi%2C%20Louis%20Brus%20and%20Alexei%20Ekimov%20have%20been%20awarded%20Nobel%20Prize%20for%20Chemistry%20for%20%26quot%3Bdiscovery%20and%20synthesis%20of%20quantum%20dots%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESwedish%20media%20outlets%20on%20Wednesday%20published%20what%20they%20reported%20were%20the%20seemingly%20leaked%20names%20of%20this%20year's%20Nobel%20chemistry%20prize%20recipients%2C%20hours%20before%20the%20laureates%20were%20to%20be%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENobel%20leaks%20are%20rare%2C%20with%20the%20various%20prize-awarding%20academies%20going%20to%20great%20lengths%20to%20keep%20the%20winners'%20names%20under%20wraps%20until%20the%20announcements.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EQuantum%20dots%20are%20widely%20used%20in%20areas%20such%20as%20modern%20LED%20television%20screens%2C%20solar%20panels%20and%20in%20medicine%20where%20they%20among%20other%20things%20can%20help%20guide%20surgeons%20removing%20tumours.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20prize%2C%20which%20was%20raised%20this%20year%20to%2011%20million%20Swedish%20crowns%20(about%20%241%20millio