0more%20than%208%20years%20in%20jail.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A61%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67003463%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67003463.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67003463.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Still%20Haven't%20Been%20Given%20Copy%20of%20FIR%2C%20Details%20of%20Offences%3A%20Newsclick%20in%20Official%20Statement%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F04143738%2FUntitled-design-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cem%3ENewsclick%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20independent%20news%20website%2C%20editors%2C%20journalists%2C%20part-time%20employees%20and%20contributors%20of%20which%20were%20targeted%20and%20subjected%20to%20raids%2C%20device%20seizures%2C%20questioning%20and%20arrests%20a%20day%20ago%2C%20has%20released%20a%20statement%20noting%20they%20are%20still%20in%20the%20dark%20over%20the%20case%20which%20led%20to%20Delhi%20Police%E2%80%99s%20action%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20statement%2C%20released%20a%20day%20after%20the%20website%E2%80%99s%20director%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20and%20one%20Amit%20Chakraborty%20were%20arrested%2C%20said%20that%20Newsclick%20has%20not%20yet%20been%20provided%20with%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20first%20information%20report%20against%20it%20or%20%E2%80%9Cinformed%20about%20the%20exact%20particulars%20of%20the%20offences%20with%20which%20we%20have%20been%20charged.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20we%20have%20been%20able%20to%20gather%20is%20that%20Newsclick%20stands%20accused%20of%20offences%20under%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20Prevention%20Act%20(UAPA)%2C%20for%20purportedly%20carrying%20Chinese%20propaganda%20on%20its%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20strongly%20condemn%20these%20actions%20of%20a%20Government%20that%20refuses%20to%20respect%20journalistic%20independence%2C%20and%20treats%20criticism%20as%20sedition%20or%20%E2%80%9Canti-national%E2%80%9D%20propaganda.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20learnt%20that%20the%20action%20is%20in%20connection%20with%20FIR%20number%20224%2F2023%2C%20which%20invokes%20sections%20of%20the%20draconian%20UAPA.%C2%A0The%20FIR%2C%20it%20is%20believed%2C%20has%20its%20roots%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F08%2F05%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fneville-roy-singham-china-propaganda.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20August%20which%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-mp-nishikant-dubey-rahul-gandhi-newsclick-independent-journalists-chinese-links-nyt-report%5C%22%3E%20BJP%20MP%20Nishikant%20Dubey%3C%2Fa%3E%20cited%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20to%20claim%20that%20Congress%20leaders%20and%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0had%20received%20funds%20from%20China%20to%20create%20an%20%E2%80%9Canti-India%E2%80%9D%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20notes%20that%20all%20journalistic%20content%20ever%20published%20on%20the%20%3Cem%3ENewsclick%3C%2Fem%3E%20website%20is%20available%20on%20the%20internet%2C%20and%20can%20be%20seen%20by%20anyone%20and%20that%2C%20notably%2C%20police%20did%20not%20appear%20to%20focus%20on%20this%20%E2%80%98Chinese%20propaganda%E2%80%99%20angle%20during%20questioning.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Special%20Cell%20of%20Delhi%20Police%20has%20not%20referred%20to%20a%20single%20article%20or%20video%20that%20they%20consider%20to%20be%20Chinese%20propaganda.%20Indeed%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fnewsclick-raids-journos-questioned-delhi-riots-farmers-protest-covid-crisis%5C%22%3Eline%20of%20questioning%20adopted%20by%20the%20Special%20Cell%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Police%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20regarding%20reportage%20on%20the%20Delhi%20riots%2C%20the%20farmers%20protests%20etc.%2C%20all%20demonstrate%20the%20motivated%20and%20malicious%20intent%20behind%20the%20present%20proceedings.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20raids%20on%20October%203%20began%20early%20in%20the%20morning%20and%20involved%20over%2040%20locations%20across%20Delhi%20and%20Mumbai.%20In%20total%2C%2037%20men%20and%20nine%20women%20were%20raided%20and%20questioned%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDevices%20belonging%20to%20staffers%20old%20and%20new%20were%20seized%20by%20police.%20Some%20journalists%20were%20taken%20to%20the%20Delhi%20Police%E2%80%99s%20Special%20Cell%20at%20Lodhi%20Road%20for%20questioning%20%E2%80%93%20which%20continued%20until%20late%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENewsclick%20noted%20that%20there%20was%20no%20adherence%20to%20due%20process%20when%20the%20devices%20were%20seized%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EElectronic%20devices%20were%20seized%20from%20the%20Newsclick%20premises%20and%20homes%20of%20employees%2C%20without%20any%20adherence%20to%20due%20process%20such%20as%20the%20provision%20of%20seizure%20memos%2C%20hash%20values%20of%20the%20seized%20data%2C%20or%20even%20copies%20of%20the%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20also%20said%20that%20its%20office%20has%20also%20been%20sealed%2C%20in%20what%20it%20called%20was%20a%20blatant%20attempt%20at%20preventing%20them%20%E2%80%9Cfrom%20continuing%20%5Btheir%5D%20reporting.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20noted%20that%20the%20website%20has%20been%20targeted%20before%20but%20that%20little%20headway%20was%20made%20in%20this%20regard%2C%20even%20though%20seizures%20happened%20then%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENewsclick%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20been%20targeted%20by%20a%20series%20of%20actions%20by%20various%20agencies%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20since%202021.%20Its%20offices%20and%20residences%20of%20officials%20have%20been%20raided%20by%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%2C%20the%20Economic%20Offences%20Wing%20of%20Delhi%20Police%20and%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20devices%2C%20laptops%2C%20gadgets%2C%20phones%2C%20etc.%20have%20been%20seized%20in%20the%20past.%20All%20emails%20and%20communications%20have%20been%20analysed%20under%20the%20microscope.%20All%20bank%20statements%2C%20invoices%2C%20expenses%20incurred%2C%20sources%20of%20funds%20received%20by%20Newsclick%20in%20the%20last%20several%20years%20have%20been%20scrutinised%20by%20different%20agencies%20of%20the%20Government%20from%20time%20to%20time.%20Various%20directors%20and%20other%20related%20persons%20have%20spent%20countless%20hours%20on%20several%20occasions%20being%20interrogated%20by%20these%20government%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20observes%20that%20in%20spite%20of%20such%20action%2C%20in%20the%20last%20two%20plus%20years%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20file%20a%20complaint%20accusing%20Newsclick%20of%20money%20laundering.%E2%80%9D%20Nor%20has%20the%20Economic%20Offences%20Wing%20of%20Delhi%20Police%20been%20able%20to%20file%20a%20charge%20sheet%20against%20Newsclick%20for%20offences%20under%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20or%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Department%20been%20able%20to%20defend%20its%20actions%20before%20the%20courts%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20last%20several%20months%2C%20Mr.%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20has%20not%20even%20been%20called%20in%20for%20questioning%20by%20any%20of%20these%20agencies%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENewsclick%20has%20called%20the%20%3Cem%3ENYT%3C%2Fem%3E%20article%20%E2%80%9Cmotivated%20and%20bogus.%E2%80%9D%20Notably%2C%20there%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fmanolo_realengo%2Fstatus%2F1709334268332110058%3Fs%3D46%26t%3DZJCJhEAnpz0jFlEdwtO2BQ%5C%22%3Eprotests%20outside%20the%20NYT%E2%80%99s%20offices%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20over%20the%20article%20and%20its%20repercussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20a%20Government%20that%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20substantiate%20any%20charges%20against%20Newsclick%20despite%20being%20in%20possession%20of%20all%20its%20information%2C%20documentation%20and%20communications%2C%20needed%20a%20motivated%20and%20bogus%20article%20published%20in%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20to%20invoke%20the%20draconian%20UAPA%20and%20attempt%20to%20shut%20down%20and%20stifle%20independent%20and%20fearless%20voices%20that%20portray%20the%20story%20of%20the%20real%20India%20%E2%80%93%20of%20peasants%2C%20of%20labourers%2C%20of%20farmers%2C%20and%20other%20oft-ignored%20sections%20of%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20statement%2C%20Newsclick%20has%20said%20that%20it%20wants%20to%20state%20for%20the%20record%2C%20the%20following%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E1.%20Newsclick%20is%20an%20independent%20news%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E2.%20Our%20journalistic%20content%20is%20based%20on%20highest%20standards%20of%20the%20profession.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E3.%20Newsclick%20does%20not%20publish%20any%20news%20or%20information%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20any%20Chinese%20entity%20or%20authority%2C%20directly%20or%20indirectly.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E4.%20Newsclick%20does%20not%20propagate%20Chinese%20propaganda%20on%20its%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E5.%20Newsclick%20does%20not%20take%20directions%20from%20Neville%20Roy%20Singham%20regarding%20the%20content%20published%20on%20its%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E6.%20All%20funding%20received%20by%20Newsclick%20has%20been%20through%20the%20appropriate%20banking%20channels%20and%20have%20been%20reported%20to%20the%20relevant%20authorities%20as%20required%20by%20law%2C%20as%20substantiated%20by%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20in%20proceedings%20before%20the%20High%20Court%20of%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20ends%20with%20the%20words%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20full%20faith%20in%20the%20Courts%20and%20the%20judicial%20process.%20We%20will%20fight%20for%20our%20journalistic%20freedom%20and%20our%20lives%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696411803000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F04143738%2FUntitled-design-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fnewsclick-fir-china-delhi-police-attack-on-media%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'We%20strongly%20condemn%20these%20actions%20of%20a%20Government%20that%20refuses%20to%20respect%20journalistic%20independence%2C%20and%20treats%20criticism%20as%20sedition%20or%20'anti-national'%20propaganda.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fnewsclick-fir-china-delhi-police-attack-on-media%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20sure-fire%20way%20to%20save%20America%E2%80%99s%20cities%3F%20Do%20what%20Tokyo%20does.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%20Japanese%20building%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20U.S.%20city%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651c8a3142ecf94db47733d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhat's%20Tokyo's%20secret%3F%20Liberal%20and%20centralized%20land-use%20policies%20that%20give%20developers%20a%20lot%20of%20power%20to%20build%20what%20they%20want%2C%20when%20they%20want.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECities%20across%20the%20US%20are%20flailing%20under%20a%20worsening%20housing%20affordability%20crisis.%20Superstar%20metropolises%20from%20Los%20Angeles%20to%20Miami%20are%20becoming%20playgrounds%20for%20the%20elite.%20Americans%20fleeing%20New%20York%20and%20San%20Francisco%20for%20more%20affordable%20lives%20in%20the%20Sunbelt%20are%20experiencing%20sticker%20shock.%20The%20median%20home%20price%20in%20the%20US%20has%20jumped%2052%25%20just%20since%20January%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20affordability%20isn't%20an%20issue%20in%20the%20world's%20biggest%20city%2C%20Tokyo.%20Despite%20facing%20many%20of%20the%20same%20pressures%20of%20scarce%20land%20and%20a%20growing%20population%2C%20the%20city%20of%2014%20million%20builds%20much%20more%20housing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20much%20more%20quickly%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0than%20US%20cities%20do.%20Since%20the%201960s%2C%20Tokyo%20has%20tripled%20its%20housing%20supply%2C%20while%20New%20York's%20has%20grown%20by%20only%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffurmancenter.org%2Fthestoop%2Fentry%2Freport-growth-in-nycs-housing-stock-is-outpaced-by-growth-in-adult-populati%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOnly%2520about%2520eight%2520percent%2520of%2Cstock%2520was%2520built%2520before%25201960.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabout%20a%20third%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20because%20housing%20is%20far%20more%20abundant%20in%20Japan's%20capital%2C%20it's%20also%20cheaper.%20The%20median%20Japanese%20tenant%20spends%20about%2020%25%20of%20their%20disposable%20income%20on%20rent%20(in%20America%20it's%2030%25).%20Rent%20for%20a%20studio%20or%20one-bedroom%20apartment%20in%20Tokyo%2C%20which%20Americans%20are%20fawning%20over%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.noahpinion.blog%2Fp%2Ftokyo-is-the-new-paris%3Futm_source%3Dsubstack%26utm_medium%3Demail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20new%20Paris%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20quarter%20of%20what%20it%20is%20in%20New%20York.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%2C%20when%20New%20York%20City%20Mayor%20Eric%20Adams%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-city-real-estate-prices-housing-apartments-eric-adams-2023-9%5C%22%3Eunveiled%20his%20plan%20to%20build%20100%2C000%20new%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20pointed%20enviously%20to%20Tokyo's%20ability%20to%20keep%20%26quot%3Bhousing%20costs%20down%20by%20increasing%20the%20supply%20of%20housing.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BHow%20are%20we%20allowing%20Tokyo%20to%20do%20things%20better%20than%20us%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHousing%20advocates%20across%20America%20are%20starting%20to%20ask%20the%20same%20question.%20Part%20of%20the%20answer%20is%20that%20build-happy%20Tokyo%20isn't%20in%20control%20of%20its%20own%20housing%20policies.%20And%20most%20of%20what%20happens%20in%20Tokyo%20would%20be%20illegal%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESimple%20and%20centralized%20zoning%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what's%20Tokyo's%20secret%3F%20Experts%20say%20it%20mostly%20comes%20down%20to%20liberal%20and%20centralized%20land-use%20policies%2C%20shaped%20over%20decades%2C%20that%20give%20developers%20a%20lot%20of%20power%20to%20build%20what%20they%20want%2C%20when%20they%20want.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThirty%20percent%20of%20homes%20in%20Japan's%20urban%20areas%20were%20destroyed%20in%20World%20War%20II.%20As%20the%20country%20attempted%20to%20rapidly%20rebuild%20itself%2C%20families%20started%20to%20grow%20and%20a%20large%20portion%20of%20the%20population%20migrated%20from%20rural%20areas%20to%20Tokyo%20and%20a%20few%20other%20major%20cities%20for%20better%20jobs%2C%20exacerbating%20an%20already%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fjapan-rental-housing-markets%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520third%2520defining%2520factor%2520is%2C1949%2520exacerbated%2520the%2520housing%2520shortage.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esevere%20housing%20shortage%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20the%20federal%20government%20stepped%20in%2C%20set%20a%20simple%20and%20permissive%20set%20of%20zoning%20and%20land-use%20laws%2C%20and%20built%20thousands%20of%20public%20housing%20complexes%2C%20known%20as%20danchi%2C%20largely%20in%20the%20Tokyo%20suburbs.%20The%20government%20also%20introduced%20housing%20finance%2C%20offering%20homebuyers%20long-term%20fixed-rate%20mortgages.%20Decades%20later%2C%20when%20the%20housing%20bubble%20of%20the%201980s%20popped%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2005%2F12%2F25%2Fbusiness%2Fyourmoney%2Ftake-it-from-japan-bubbles-hurt.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflattened%20Japan's%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20government%20deregulated%20its%20housing%20policies%20even%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20really%20sets%20Japanese%20housing%20policy%20apart%20from%20other%20advanced%20democracies%20is%20%26quot%3Bthe%20extreme%20concentration%20of%20decision-making%20at%20the%20national%20level%2C%26quot%3B%20Alan%20Durning%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20pro-housing%20non-profit%20Sightline%20Institute%2C%20told%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20city%20councils%20make%20much%20of%20our%20housing%20policy.%20This%20gives%20immense%20power%20to%20existing%20residents%2C%20mostly%20homeowners%2C%20who%20vote%20in%20council%20elections%20and%20show%20up%20to%20community%20meetings%20to%20determine%20what%20gets%20built.%20Between%20the%20endless%20bickering%2C%20hyperlocal%20zoning%20regulations%2C%20historic%20preservation%20laws%2C%20and%20environmental%20reviews%2C%20much%20proposed%20new%20housing%20development%20gets%20dragged%20out%20or%20outright%20killed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJapan%20is%20the%20exact%20opposite%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Durning.%20In%20collectivist%20Japan%2C%20housing%20policy%20is%20designed%20to%20benefit%20the%20most%20people%20possible.%20When%20national%20authorities%20make%20the%20decisions%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20broader%20community's%20interest%20in%20having%20an%20abundance%20of%20housing%20outweighs%20the%20opposition%20of%20neighbors%2C%26quot%3B%20Durning%20said.%20If%20neighbors%20complain%20about%20a%20new%20apartment%20building%20going%20up%20on%20their%20block%2C%20tough%20luck.%20%26quot%3BLocal%20government%20officials%20will%20say%2C%20'Oh%2C%20I%20cannot%20do%20anything%20for%20you%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Jiro%20Yoshida%2C%20a%20business%20professor%20at%20Pennsylvania%20State%20University.%20In%20Japan%2C%20NIMBYism%20can't%20exist.%20Centralized%20zoning%20leads%20to%20more%20inclusive%20outcomes%2C%20while%20handing%20power%20to%20local%20interests%20tends%20to%20worsen%20inequity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20the%20US%20has%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20different%20zoning%20systems%20across%20the%20country%2C%20Japan%20has%2012.%20(Granted%2C%20Japan%20is%20geographically%20about%20the%20size%20of%20Montana%2C%20but%20it%20also%20has%20nearly%2040%25%20of%20the%20US%20population.)%20For%20most%20of%20those%20dozen%2C%20there%20are%20very%20few%20restrictions%20on%20mixing%20commercial%20and%20residential%20construction.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20much%20more%20typical%20to%20see%20a%2010-story%20apartment%20building%20with%20small%20studio%20apartments%2C%20and%20then%20a%20two-story%20house%2C%20and%20then%20a%20small%20commercial%20building%20with%20a%20restaurant%20or%20a%20grocery%20store%20right%20next%20to%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jenny%20Schuetz%2C%20an%20expert%20in%20urban%20economics%20and%20housing%20policy%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Yoshida%20moved%20from%20Tokyo%20to%20the%20US%2C%20he%20said%20he%20was%20shocked%20to%20discover%20the%20existence%20of%20two%20species%20never%20before%20spotted%20in%20Japan%3A%20land-use%20attorneys%20and%20permit%20expeditors.%20We%20have%20a%20whole%20ecosystem%20of%20professionals%20who%20make%20a%20living%20helping%20property%20owners%20navigate%20byzantine%20regulations%2C%20from%20real-estate%20attorneys%20to%20construction%20consultants.%20%26quot%3BThat%20means%20that%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20negotiation%2C%20and%20discretion%2C%20and%20uncertainty%20around%20the%20building%20permits%20and%20development%20entitlement%26quot%3B%20process%2C%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20have%20a%20term%20for%20the%20types%20of%20buildings%20that%20fall%20between%20single-family%20homes%20and%20high-rise%20apartments%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bmissing%20middle%20housing.%26quot%3B%20This%20term%20doesn't%20exist%20in%20Japan%2C%20because%20middle%20housing%20is%20far%20from%20missing.%20It's%20abundant%2C%20largely%20because%20it's%20legal%20and%20much%20cheaper%20and%20more%20efficient%20to%20build.%20The%20more%20builders%20construct%20the%20same%20type%20of%20structure%2C%20the%20faster%20and%20cheaper%20they%20can%20do%20it.%20Standardized%20zoning%20for%20multi-family%20housing%20would%20make%20building%20it%20much%20cheaper%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Schuetz%20said.%20The%20longer%20a%20developer%20spends%20tied%20up%20in%20regulatory%20processes%2C%20the%20higher%20the%20eventual%20project%20costs%20are.%20%26quot%3BThe%20type%20of%20housing%20that's%20cheapest%20and%20fastest%20to%20build%20in%20the%20US%20are%20single-family%20detached%20homes%20in%20subdivisions%2C%20because%20builders%20reproduce%20exactly%20the%20same%20house%20thousands%20of%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20It%20helps%20that%20most%20Tokyo%20residents%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fheatmap.news%2Feconomy%2Ftokyo-anti-car-pedestrian-paradise%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edon't%20own%20cars%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20parking%20doesn't%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fparking-requirements-and-foundations-are-driving-up-the-cost-of-multifamily-housing%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einflate%20the%20price%20of%20housing%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20much%20as%20it%20does%20in%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndr%C3%A9%20Sorensen%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20geography%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto%2C%20argues%20there's%20a%20%26quot%3Bmore%20important%20factor%26quot%3B%20in%20housing%20affordability%20than%20flexible%20zoning%20laws%3A%20An%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnews%2Fjapans-aging-population-is-shrinking-at-a-record-rate%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DJapan%2527s%2520overall%2520population%2520fell%2520to%2Cprevious%2520year%252C%2520the%2520study%2520shows.%26amp%3Btext%3DJapan%2520has%2520the%2520fastest%252Daging%2Cto%2520decline%2520in%2520the%25201970s.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaging%20and%20shrinking%20population%3C%2Fa%3E%20countrywide.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20there%20are%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasia.nikkei.com%2FSpotlight%2FDatawatch%2FMore-empty-homes-Japan-s-housing-glut-to-hit-10m-in-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabout%2010%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20vacant%20homes%20across%20the%20country.%20With%20Tokyo's%20comprehensive%20mass%20transit%2C%20vacant%20homes%20in%20the%20suburbs%20offer%20Tokyo%20workers%20cheaper%20housing%20options%20just%20outside%20the%20city%2C%20says%20Sorensen.%C2%A0%20%26quot%3BIf%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20abandoned%20housing%20in%20the%20suburbs%2C%20then%20that's%20going%20to%20also%20restrain%20upward%20pressure%20on%20prices%20in%20the%20center.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEarthquakes%20and%20small%20homes%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20feature%20of%20the%20Japanese%20housing%20market%20is%20purely%20situational%3A%20The%20country%20is%20a%20hotspot%20for%20earthquakes.%20After%20major%20seismic%20events%2C%20Japan%20updates%20its%20national%20building%20codes.%20Because%20these%20codes%20apply%20to%20virtually%20all%20buildings%2C%20older%20buildings%20quickly%20become%20non-compliant%20and%20unattractive%20to%20renters%20and%20buyers%20who%20want%20to%20live%20in%20safe%20homes.%20In%20America%2C%20the%20average%20age%20of%20a%20demolished%20building%20is%2067%20years%2C%20Yoshida%20found.%20In%20Japan%2C%20it's%2032.%20The%20average%20home%20is%20significantly%20younger%20than%20the%20average%20Japanese%20resident.%20More%20demolition%20means%20more%20construction.%20%26quot%3BIn%20any%20100%20year%20period%2C%20you%20have%20a%20lot%20more%20opportunities%20to%20replace%20a%20building%20with%20something%20much%20bigger%2C%26quot%3B%20Durning%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EIn%20America%2C%20the%20average%20age%20of%20a%20demolished%20building%20is%2067%20years.%20In%20Japan%2C%20it's%2032.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20because%20of%20its%20history%20of%20earthquakes%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjapantoday.com%2Fcategory%2Ffeatures%2Flifestyle%2Fhow-the-great-fire-of-1657-shaped-modern-tokyo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efires%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there's%20a%20much%20broader%20acceptance%20of%20the%20impermanence%20of%20buildings.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20a%20premium%20associated%20with%20older%20housing%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nolan%20Gray%2C%20a%20city%20planner%20and%20research%20director%20for%20California%20YIMBY.%20In%20fact%2C%20older%20homes%20are%20referred%20to%20as%20%26quot%3Bused%26quot%3B%20housing.%20While%20pre-war%20apartments%20in%20New%20York%20are%20coveted%20for%20their%20history%20and%20unique%20details%2C%20pre-war%20homes%20in%20Japan%20are%20largely%20considered%20unsafe%20and%20undesirable.%20Even%20the%20country's%20holiest%20structure%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20Ise-Jingu%20Shinto%20shrine%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fagenda%2F2019%2F04%2Fjapans-holiest-shrine-is-pulled-down-and-rebuilt-every-20-years-on-purpose%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edemolished%20and%20rebuilt%3C%2Fa%3E%20every%2020%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImpermanence%20also%20means%20that%20most%20homes%20depreciate%20in%20value%20quickly.%20Japanese%20homeowners%20largely%20don't%20rely%20on%20selling%20their%20homes%20to%20fund%20their%20retirement%20the%20way%20Americans%20do.%20Loose%20zoning%2C%20abundant%20supply%2C%20and%20low%20housing%20costs%20aren't%20as%20in%20tension%20with%20Japanese%20homeowners'%20interests.%20As%20Durning%20notes%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20with%20housing%20policy%20in%20the%20United%20States%20is%20that%20it's%20not%20actually%20about%20housing%2C%20it's%20about%20real%20estate%20investment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDifferent%20cultural%20norms%20and%20preferences%20also%20set%20Japanese%20housing%20apart.%20Americans%20tend%20to%20like%20living%20in%20much%20larger%20spaces.%20Or%2C%20at%20least%2C%20that's%20what%20the%20market%20provides.%20In%20Tokyo%2C%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fgraphics%2FHEALTH-CORONAVIRUS%2FTOKYO-HOMES%2Fdgkvlabxpbx%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%20a%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20small%20studios%20and%20even%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F10%2F03%2Fbusiness%2Ftiny-apartments-tokyo.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emicro-apartments%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20100%20square%20feet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECould%20the%20US%20import%20Japanese%20housing%20policy%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20policymakers%20don't%20often%20look%20to%20learn%20from%20other%20countries.%20%26quot%3BThe%20US%20is%20sort%20of%20famously%20insular%20in%20its%20political%20discourse%2C%26quot%3B%20Durning%20says.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20call%20it%20American%20exceptionalism%20or%20you%20can%20call%20it%20blindness%20of%20the%20imperial%20state.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20do%20look%20abroad%2C%20urban%20planners%20have%20traditionally%20relied%20on%20European%20examples.%20But%20many%20European%20cities%20aren't%20facing%20the%20same%20pressures%20of%20a%20fast-growing%20population%20and%20dynamic%20economy%20that%20American%20cities%20are.%20Vienna%2C%20which%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huduser.gov%2Fportal%2Fpdredge%2Fpdr_edge_featd_article_011314.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20housing%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20many%20Democrats%20celebrate%20as%20a%20model%2C%20isn't%20facing%20rapid%20population%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Durning%20says%20that's%20starting%20to%20change.%20As%20the%20US%20housing%20crisis%20has%20intensified%2C%20a%20few%20prominent%20experts%2C%20including%20Yoshida%20and%20Durning%2C%20have%20elevated%20Japan's%20approach%20to%20building.%20Japan's%20housing%20policy%20%26quot%3Bis%20now%20quite%20well%20understood%26quot%3B%20among%20American%20housing%20advocates%20and%20scholars%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhereas%20it%20was%20not%20even%20three%20years%20ago.%26quot%3B%20Gray%20thinks%20there's%20some%20combination%20of%20policies%20and%20design%20from%20around%20the%20world%20that%20would%20create%20the%20most%20liveable%20and%20inclusive%20cities.%20%26quot%3BThe%20best%20city%20combines%20Amsterdam%20public%20realm%20design%20with%20Tokyo-style%20land-use%20flexibility%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20American%20consumers%20probably%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20live%20in%20the%20studio%20or%20one-bedroom%20apartments%20that%20Japanese%20people%20just%20sort%20of%20take%20for%20granted%2C%26quot%3B%20Schuetz%20said.%20But%2C%20she%20added%2C%20we%20shouldn't%20have%20many%20of%20the%20minimum%20size%20regulations%20we%20have.%20Instead%2C%20we%20should%20let%20consumers%20decide%20what%20tradeoffs%20they're%20willing%20to%20make.%20%26quot%3BAllow%20the%20market%20to%20build%20stuff%2C%20and%20the%20market%20will%20figure%20out%20what%20people%20are%20willing%20to%20pay%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECity%20planners%20and%20housing%20researchers%20also%20say%20the%20US%20could%20move%20towards%20the%20Japanese%20model%20of%20centralized%20and%20non-restrictive%20zoning.%20Some%20states%20already%20have.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fin-california-statewide-housing-reforms-brush-against-local-resistance%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECalifornia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opb.org%2Farticle%2F2023%2F02%2F24%2Foregon-leaders-rethink-housing-generation-old-approach-building%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOregon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.seattletimes.com%2Fseattle-news%2Fpolitics%2Fwa-senate-passes-bill-allowing-duplexes-fourplexes-in-single-family-zones%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWashington%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmontana-republicans-anti-california-message-pro-housing-affordability-building-density-2023-4%5C%22%3EMontana%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20%26quot%3Bbacking%20their%20way%20into%20a%20statewide%20system%20of%20zoning%26quot%3B%20by%20passing%20a%20slew%20of%20state-wide%20housing%20reforms%2C%20including%20legalizing%20denser%20and%20more%20mixed-use%20neighborhoods%2C%20Gray%20noted.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20kind%20of%20accidentally%20building%20a%20Japanese-style%20zoning%20system%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Feliza-relman%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22c19804eacd372b9cf134b701ab612126%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Feliza-relman%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3EEliza%20Relman%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20policy%20correspondent%20focused%20on%20housing%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20on%20Insider's%20economy%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-build-like-tokyo-housing-crisis-doom-loop-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696411801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651c8a1a42ecf94db