s%20been%20detained%20since%20July%202022%2C%20also%20under%20the%20UAPA%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20USCIRF%20vice-chair%20Frederick%20A.%20Davie.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CUSCIRF%20calls%20on%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20evaluate%20these%20cases%20and%20to%20release%20all%20prisoners%20of%20conscience%20and%20those%20detained%20for%20peacefully%20expressing%20their%20religion%20or%20belief.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20June%202020%2C%20USCIRF%20has%20called%20on%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20to%20designate%20India%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9CCountry%20of%20Particular%20Concern%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Csystematic%2C%20ongoing%2C%20and%20egregious%20violations%20of%20religious%20freedom%E2%80%9D.%20In%20May%20this%20year%2C%20for%20the%20fourth%20consecutive%20year%2C%20USCIRF%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fuscirf-country-of-particular-concern-fourth-time%5C%22%3Eadvised%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20US%20administration%20should%20designate%20India%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98Country%20of%20Particular%20Concern%2C%E2%80%99%20despite%20this%20recommendation%20not%20having%20been%20accepted%20since%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696404653000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F02105412%2F1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fuscirf-once-again-raises-concern-over-declining-religious-freedom-in-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20United%20States%20Commission%20on%20International%20Religious%20Freedom%20has%20called%20on%20the%20Modi%20government%20to%20release%2037%20individuals%20across%20multiple%20faiths%20jailed%20for%20the%20'peaceful%20exercise%20of%20their%20freedom%20of%20religion%20or%20belief'.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fuscirf-once-again-raises-concern-over-declining-religious-freedom-in-india%22%2C%22cdn